lillycoder (0.1.4-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * REPL: end every assistant turn on a fresh line so the prompt no
    longer runs into lilly's last token.
  * Agent: announce each tool call before dispatch ("⏳ name(args)")
    instead of only logging the result, so long-running write/bash
    calls no longer look hung.
  * Reasoning tokens: render <think>...</think> segments and the
    OpenAI-style delta.reasoning_content field as dim grey output.
    Hidden by default; toggle with /thoughts (also accepts on/off),
    persisted in config.toml under [ui].
  * Ctrl+C now interrupts the current turn and returns to the prompt
    instead of crashing out with a traceback. Two Ctrl+Cs within 2
    seconds exit the session (Ctrl+D still exits immediately).
  * Permission prompt: stop swallowing the option keys to Rich markup.
    "[y]es / [n]o / [a]lways / [p]ath" now reads as "(y)es / (n)o /
    (a)lways / (p)ath", and the call summary is printed without
    markup parsing so paths/content with brackets render correctly.

 -- Ramazan Yavuz <yavuzramazan1994@gmail.com>  Wed, 06 May 2026 18:30:00 +0000

lillycoder (0.1.3-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Context window is now read from the server instead of hardcoded to
    8192. Uses /v1/models meta (n_ctx, n_ctx_train) and falls back to
    llama.cpp /props for the runtime n_ctx. Also accepts top-level
    context_length / max_context_length / context_window keys.
  * Banner now shows the active context size and whether it came from
    the server or the 8k fallback.

 -- Ramazan Yavuz <yavuzramazan1994@gmail.com>  Wed, 06 May 2026 17:00:00 +0000

lillycoder (0.1.2-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * REPL: add /setpersona for switching personas mid-session.
    Three forms: /setpersona <name> (saved persona), /setpersona -f <path>
    (load from a file), /setpersona <text...> (inline text). Also /personas
    lists saved personas and marks the active one.

 -- Ramazan Yavuz <yavuzramazan1994@gmail.com>  Wed, 06 May 2026 16:30:00 +0000

lillycoder (0.1.1-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Discovery: probe more default LLM server ports out of the box -
    8000 (vLLM, text-generation-webui), 5001 (koboldcpp), 4891 (GPT4All),
    11435 (ollama secondary), 9090/9091 (mlx-lm), and 18092 (allm).
  * REPL: show a "lilly is thinking..." spinner from request send until
    the first token (or first tool call) arrives, so it's clear the
    model is working rather than hung.

 -- Ramazan Yavuz <yavuzramazan1994@gmail.com>  Wed, 06 May 2026 16:00:00 +0000

lillycoder (0.1.0-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Initial release.
  * REPL with 11 tools: read_file, list_dir, grep, find, write_file,
    edit_file, mkdir, mv, rm, bash, pkg_install.
  * Auto-discovery of local OpenAI-compatible LLM servers on common ports.
  * Per-tool permission prompts with [y/n/always-tool/always-path] choices,
    persisted per-project.
  * Hard-deny safety classifier (sudo, rm -rf /, mkfs, fork bombs, etc.)
    that cannot be turned off by --bypass-permissions.
  * Tool-call capability allowlist warns on models without native function
    calling.
  * Per-project session history at .lillycoder/history.jsonl.
  * Auto-compaction of context above 90% of the model window.
  * Bundled default persona (kid-coder voice); user personas under
    ~/.config/lillycoder/personas/.

 -- Ramazan Yavuz <yavuzramazan1994@gmail.com>  Wed, 06 May 2026 14:50:00 +0000
